The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, March 15, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																The Show				 																																	(ITC Sangeet Research Academy, March 16, 6 -10 pm)				 																																	lA whole host of Holi dhrupads, dhamars, bandishes and Basant Ritu compositions will be performed by a star-studded cast of singers and musicians, including Falguni Mitra, Shubha Mudgal (picture above), Abdul Rashid Khan and Supratik Sengupta				 																The Concert				 																																	(Gyan Manch, March 15, 7 pm)				 																																	lA Blues Musical Evening is the debut concert of singer-lyricist Joy Bhaduris new art podium and rhythm and blues band. Also featuring Nondon Bagchi on drums and Sougata Roy Chowdhury on sarod as guest artistes, the show will focus on original scores, composed by the free-lance expressionist who works with leprosy victims and streetchildren				 																The Book				 																																	(Ismail Merchant)				 																																	lThe man from Mumbai who built a name for himself in Hollywood with 31 Oscar nominations, has made his mark on the international movie industry through his own brand of independent films. This is Ismail Merchants story, which tells the extraordinary tale of a boy who made his own dreams come true.				 																The CD				 																																	(Agni)				 																																	lA tribute to the departed members of the band  bassist Juggie and manager Mundy, killed in a car crash  all the songs in this album are based on classical ragas, without using any Indian instruments
